  description: {
    en: 'This maze can be solved as follows: \
     Walk straight until you hit a wall, then jump to the label "guess". \
     After execution, "guess" writes 0 or 1 in the variable "result" and jumps back to the label "done". <br/>\
     If you get the number 0 you have to turn left. If the result is 1, you have to turn right to get to the destination. \
     <remark hidden="true">The functionality of "guess" is not relevant here.</remark>',
    de: 'The task now is to find your way out of the maze with the given subprogram "guess"!\
     Whenever you can no longer walk straight, jump to the label "guess". \
     After execution, "guess" writes 0 or 1 in the variable result and jumps back to the label "done". \
     If you get the number 0 you have to turn left. If the result is 1, you have to turn right to get to the destination. \
     <remark hidden="true">The functionality of "guess" is not relevant here.</remark>'
